hopobject.body: I'm interested in this position proto-col clinic westbury In the middle chapters there’s a certain confusion between the broad church of Freudian phallic symbolism, which extends to things like hats, overcoats and even the number three, and what you might call the Looking like A Penis sense of the term – though obviously several skyscrapers are both. But Williams is right to pick out a certain doleful refrain through these failed utopias. Partly, it’s the patriarchy’s fault: “The truth is, this so-called sexual revolution was something made up by guys and for guys,” said one Drop City resident; another asked why women had to do all the cooking. The guys might have made headway on the first part if they’d applied themselves to the second.
